Caltha poetarum: or The bumble bee. Composed by T. Cutvvode Esquyre Caltha poetarum. Dymoke, Tailboys, attributed name.
[80] p.
Printed by Thomas Creede, for Richard Oliue, London : 1599.
T. Cutwode, probably a pseudonym, has been identified with Tailboys Dymoke. In verse. Signatures: A-E. The first two leaves are blank except for signature-mark "A" on the first. Reproduction of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
